      "content": "{\"claim\": \"The harness strictly beats self-consistency only when the critic employs multi-round adjudication with sequential veto attempts on remaining candidates, rather than a single pass, reducing the wrong-majority retention probability exponentially in rounds.\",\"mechanism\": \"The repository's data show that a single-round critic veto with fixed precision 0.125 and recall 1.0 yields zero net benefit because the error rate is independent of the veto attempt. The causal failure is that a single pass cannot sufficiently filter wrong candidates. If instead the critic operates over T rounds, re-evaluating the remaining candidates after each veto, the probability of retaining a wrong-majority set decreases multiplicatively. The strict advantage regime is a surface: for any base error in (0.5-p, 0.5+p) where p scales with 1/sqrt(k), there exists a round count T and threshold tau making the expected net-fixed-minus-broke positive if and only if the critic's per-round error rate is less than 0.5.\",\"scope\": {\"covers\": [\"multi-round critic adjudication with T rounds\", \"sequential veto policy with threshold tau\", \"base error 0.40-0.70\", \"any k >= 5\"], \"excludes\": [\"single-round critic veto with fixed global precision/recall\", \"critic per-round error rate >= 0.5\"]},\"forbidden\": [{\"case\": \"Critic per-round error rate is >= 0.5 yet multi-round harness strictly beats self-consistency on >= 50% of questions\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}, {\"case\": \"Critic per-round error rate is < 0.5 but no number of rounds T yields positive net-fixed-minus-broke averaged over the test set\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}, {\"case\": \"The multi-round harness accuracy exceeds self-consistency but a single-round harness also exceeds self-consistency by the same margin, contradicting that multi-round adjudication is necessary\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}],\"prose_notes\": \"Experiment: reuse the repository's 44 questions plus 60 new questions spanning base error 0.30-0.70; generate k=5 candidates; instead of single-round critic veto, run the critic for T in {1, 2, 3, 4, 5} rounds; sweep tau in {0.5, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9, 0.95}; compute per-T, per-tau harness accuracy and net-fixed-minus-broke; also run the single-round harness for comparison. Confirm: (1) at T=3, retention of wrong-majority sets drops below 0.1; (2) there exists T, tau where harness strictly beats SC; (3) single-round veto does not match this. Token budget: 104 q * 5 cand * 800 tokens + 104 q * 5 * T * 600 critic + 104 q * 5 thresholds * 50 eval + analysis ~= 500k.\"}",
